WEBVTT

00:06.834 --> 00:12.417
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

00:17.458 --> 00:18.792
(CROWS CAWING)

00:33.500 --> 00:35.083
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

00:43.625 --> 00:49.667
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

00:53.166 --> 00:54.166
(SIGHS)

01:00.333 --> 01:01.500
Mrs. Carroll?

01:02.166 --> 01:03.500
Is everything all right?

01:05.333 --> 01:08.333
-(TRAIN RUMBLING)
-(WHISTLE BLOWS)

01:09.458 --> 01:10.500
(SIGHS)

01:12.208 --> 01:13.250
(DOORBELL RINGS)

01:13.333 --> 01:15.458
MARE SHEEHAN: Mrs. Carroll?
It's Mare Sheehan.

01:15.542 --> 01:17.625
I'm standing outside
your front door.

01:18.333 --> 01:20.208
In the fucking freezing cold.

01:20.291 --> 01:21.375
Mrs. Carroll?

01:28.125 --> 01:29.291
(INHALES)

01:29.375 --> 01:31.375
BETTY CARROLL: Mare?
Mare, you out there?

01:33.875 --> 01:35.583
Oh, you're here.

01:36.041 --> 01:37.792
I'm here.

01:37.875 --> 01:40.458
BETTY: I wanted to make sure
you knew about this right away

01:40.542 --> 01:42.250
so the community's safe

01:42.333 --> 01:44.458
in case the pervert
is still on the loose.

01:44.542 --> 01:47.417
Well, next time,
you just call the station.

01:47.500 --> 01:50.375
-Do you have the main number?
-I don't remember.

01:51.250 --> 01:52.959
But-- but I trust you,

01:53.041 --> 01:55.834
and I don't know who
the station will send over.

01:55.917 --> 01:57.959
I understand,
but I'm a detective sergeant,

01:58.041 --> 02:02.000
which means I investigate
the burglaries and the overdoses

02:02.083 --> 02:05.375
and all the really bad crap
that goes on around here.

02:05.458 --> 02:06.583
Sounds awful.

02:06.667 --> 02:08.500
Maybe you should look into
a different line of work.

02:08.583 --> 02:10.250
Here it is, Mrs. Carroll.
See this?

02:11.625 --> 02:13.834
That's the main station number,
all right?

02:13.917 --> 02:15.250
That's the one you want.

02:15.333 --> 02:17.917
I'll put it right in the center.

02:20.792 --> 02:22.625
So you call them, okay,

02:22.709 --> 02:24.625
next time,
instead of waking me up.

02:26.083 --> 02:30.000
So, there's
the scene of the crime,

02:30.083 --> 02:31.750
as they say in your business.

02:31.834 --> 02:34.166
My granddaughter was upstairs

02:34.250 --> 02:36.208
getting undressed
to take a shower

02:36.291 --> 02:39.542
when she looked out
the window and "Ahh!"

02:39.625 --> 02:42.667
There he is.
He was standing right out there.

02:42.750 --> 02:47.500
One of those creepy
peeper weirdos.

02:47.583 --> 02:49.792
MARE: Did your granddaughter
say anything about him or...

02:49.875 --> 02:51.542
He was wearing
a hooded sweatshirt

02:51.625 --> 02:53.375
so it was hard
to get much of his face,

02:53.458 --> 02:56.500
but from what she could see,
he looked like a ferret.

02:56.583 --> 02:59.875
-MARE: A ferret?
-That's what she said.

02:59.959 --> 03:02.792
Is that a security camera
up there?

03:02.875 --> 03:06.250
Oh, yes. We bought that
at Best Buy three months ago,

03:06.333 --> 03:09.166
but Mr. Procrastinator
hasn't figured out

03:09.250 --> 03:11.333
how to use it yet.
Big surprise.

03:12.792 --> 03:14.583
And where is
your granddaughter now?

03:14.667 --> 03:15.917
Oh, she was scared to death,

03:16.000 --> 03:18.250
so she hightailed it
back to Allentown.

03:18.333 --> 03:19.917
She didn't wanna
stay around here

03:20.000 --> 03:21.625
with a ferret on the loose.

03:22.291 --> 03:25.041
All right. Well, uh,

03:25.125 --> 03:28.875
I'll file a report and, uh,
make sure patrol's aware.

03:28.959 --> 03:31.291
I'm half tempted
to leave as well,

03:31.375 --> 03:34.166
but then I'd have to go to
my sister's place in Ridley,

03:34.250 --> 03:35.583
and she has cats.

03:35.667 --> 03:36.917
Oh, I hate cats.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.625
-No, I get that, Mrs. Carroll.
-They are disgusting animals.

03:39.709 --> 03:42.375
-You know, they're all bones.
-Good morning, Mare.

03:42.458 --> 03:43.750
-Mr. Carroll.
-Did Betty tell you

03:43.834 --> 03:45.542
what happened here this morning
with the weirdo?

03:45.625 --> 03:47.291
-Oh, of course.
-Mrs. Carroll filled me in.

03:47.375 --> 03:48.959
Of course I told her
what happened.

03:49.041 --> 03:50.875
The whole case
would've been solved

03:50.959 --> 03:52.709
if you had been
able to figure out

03:52.792 --> 03:55.125
how to set up
the security camera.

03:55.208 --> 03:57.458
-I told you
I was going to do that today.
-All right, I'm gonna...

03:57.542 --> 04:00.041
-head back to the station now
and file a report.
-(OVERLAPPING ARGUING)

04:00.125 --> 04:02.333
-We'll take care of it.
-(ARGUING CONTINUES)

04:02.417 --> 04:04.500
Hey, Mare.
Big night tonight, huh?

04:04.583 --> 04:06.834
They did a full article on you
in the Tribune.

04:06.917 --> 04:08.250
-Did you see it?
-Uh, no.

04:08.333 --> 04:09.959
GLENN CARROLL:
Oh, you gotta see it, Mare.

04:10.041 --> 04:11.667
-You got a sec?
-I don't, actually.

04:11.750 --> 04:15.625
-GLENN: Just a second.
-BETTY: Well, now, no,
just go get it for her, okay?

04:15.709 --> 04:18.583
You let him,
he would talk all day.

04:18.667 --> 04:19.875
-GLENN: Betty!
-(GROANS)

04:19.959 --> 04:21.250
GLENN:
What did you do with the paper?

04:21.333 --> 04:22.500
I left it here in the bathroom.

04:22.583 --> 04:25.291
Now you stay right here.
I'll be right back, Mare.

04:25.375 --> 04:26.875
GLENN: Where is it?
Where did you put it?

04:26.959 --> 04:28.625
BETTY: Oh, come on, Glenn.
Do I have to...

04:28.709 --> 04:32.542
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

04:35.625 --> 04:37.709
I'm gonna miss you this weekend.

04:39.667 --> 04:42.125
Who's gonna sleep next to me?

04:42.208 --> 04:46.375
And hold me, and kiss me,
and snuggle me?

04:48.083 --> 04:50.000
Hmm?

04:50.083 --> 04:54.250
Sometimes I wonder if you even
realize how much I love you.

04:55.375 --> 04:57.583
Your grandmom used to say,

04:57.667 --> 05:00.667
"You'll understand
when you're a parent."

05:00.750 --> 05:04.458
And I was always like,
"Yeah, whatever."

05:05.875 --> 05:08.834
But now it's like
you can love someone so much,

05:08.917 --> 05:11.417
-it's scary.
-(BABY DJ COOING)

05:13.250 --> 05:15.583
Oh, my God.
I'm gonna miss you so much.

05:16.667 --> 05:19.417
Okay. Let's get you changed.

05:20.625 --> 05:21.709
Whoo!

05:38.041 --> 05:39.792
-(GRUNTS)
-(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

05:41.959 --> 05:44.291
-(SIGHS)
-(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

05:50.000 --> 05:53.417
He's pissing in your car window
or someone else's car window?

05:54.458 --> 05:56.375
No, no, no, no.
Just stay in the house.

05:56.458 --> 05:58.458
An officer will be there
momentarily.

05:59.125 --> 06:00.291
Morning, Jan.

06:01.500 --> 06:02.583
See this yet?

06:02.667 --> 06:04.542
Big write-up in the Tribune
this morning.

06:04.625 --> 06:07.333
I'm gonna frame it for you
and hang it up in your office.

06:07.417 --> 06:10.000
Yeah. Please don't do that.

06:10.083 --> 06:13.917
I want us all to give a very
warm welcome to Officer Trammel.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.750
Today is his first day
out in the field.

06:16.834 --> 06:19.625
(CHEERING)

06:19.709 --> 06:21.417
CORPORAL MASTERSON:
Good luck out there, Trammel.

06:21.500 --> 06:22.458
OFFICER TRAMMEL: Thank you.

06:22.542 --> 06:24.000
MASTERSON:
All right, folks, let get to it.

06:24.083 --> 06:26.917
Uh, Mare, you had something
today, right?

06:27.000 --> 06:30.458
Uh, yeah. A prowler
at 28 Grubb Road.

06:30.542 --> 06:33.875
Homeowner said a suspicious male
was watching from the backyard

06:33.959 --> 06:36.583
as her granddaughter took
a shower early this morning.

06:36.667 --> 06:38.792
-You get a description?
-Yeah.

06:43.458 --> 06:45.166
OFFICER BOYLE:
I already caught the bastard.

06:45.250 --> 06:47.083
He's in a cage
in my daughter's bedroom.

06:47.166 --> 06:48.417
(LAUGHTER)

06:48.500 --> 06:50.291
MASTERSON: All right, all right.
Let's float a car out there

06:50.375 --> 06:52.959
between Eldridge
and Garnet Mine...

06:53.041 --> 06:54.250
What's up?

06:59.375 --> 07:02.291
DAWN BAILEY: (ON TV)
My daughter's been missing
for exactly one year today.

07:02.375 --> 07:05.083
-(CHIEF CARTER CLEARS THROAT)
-DAWN: Every moment without her

07:05.166 --> 07:06.709
has been complete torture.

07:06.792 --> 07:09.333
And the police
aren't doing anything.

07:09.417 --> 07:12.250
They don't care.
That's why we're here.

07:12.333 --> 07:15.417
If they're not gonna fight
to find Katie, we will.

07:17.417 --> 07:20.125
CARTER:
The Board of Commissioners
called again this morning

07:20.208 --> 07:23.125
about adding a county detective
to assist with the case.

07:23.208 --> 07:24.750
They want
a fresh set of eyes on this

07:24.834 --> 07:26.000
-by Monday.
-MARE: No, no, no, no, no.

07:26.083 --> 07:28.625
I don't need some county
shithead coming on my case.

07:28.709 --> 07:30.166
They're getting pressured, Mare.

07:30.250 --> 07:31.583
MARE: Oh, come on, Chief.

07:31.667 --> 07:33.500
And 'cause they're getting
pressured,

07:33.583 --> 07:35.959
-I'm getting pressured.
-MARE: Chief, come on.

07:36.709 --> 07:38.375
You know how this shit goes.

07:39.834 --> 07:41.834
Katie Bailey
was a known drug abuser

07:41.917 --> 07:44.250
with a history of prostitution.

07:44.333 --> 07:46.291
(SCOFFS) She's probably
lying at the bottom

07:46.375 --> 07:49.333
of the Delaware River right now.
We'd never know.

07:49.417 --> 07:52.750
CARTER: The thing is,
we don't know.

07:53.834 --> 07:55.083
Anything.

07:55.667 --> 07:57.667
After a year.

07:57.750 --> 08:00.417
(SCOFFS)
Thanks for being in my corner.

08:01.792 --> 08:03.250
(DOOR OPENS)

08:04.542 --> 08:05.709
(DOOR SLAMS)

08:05.792 --> 08:06.917
Sit down, Mare.

08:10.583 --> 08:13.709
The Rotary Club increased
the reward money to 15,000.

08:13.792 --> 08:16.000
We're printing up new flyers
and handing them out

08:16.083 --> 08:19.166
at every needle exchange
from Camden to Wilmington.

08:20.792 --> 08:24.500
Go back to the file.
We're starting over here.

08:26.208 --> 08:31.583
♪ (QUIET MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

08:35.667 --> 08:37.417
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

08:38.250 --> 08:39.625
Okay.

08:40.583 --> 08:43.125
-(SMOOCHES)
-(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

08:43.792 --> 08:44.792
Hey.

08:48.125 --> 08:49.875
-Hey. Come on in.
-Hi. Could you--

08:49.959 --> 08:52.625
could you just hand him over
'cause I gotta-- I gotta go.

08:54.208 --> 08:56.917
It's cold out.
You can at least stand inside.

08:58.166 --> 09:00.542
It's nice to see you too. Jeez.

09:00.625 --> 09:03.375
-(DJ COOS)
-Okay.

09:07.959 --> 09:11.333
-(DJ GIGGLES)
-(CAR HORN HONKS)

09:14.291 --> 09:15.417
What is she doing here?

09:15.500 --> 09:17.291
Don't worry about
what she's doing here.

09:17.375 --> 09:19.583
I don't ask about your life.

09:19.667 --> 09:22.041
I don't want her around my son,
okay?

09:23.417 --> 09:25.291
I seriously, like, don't even
know what you see in her.

09:25.375 --> 09:27.000
Oh, just shut up, Erin.

09:32.000 --> 09:33.417
-(DOOR SLAMS)
-(SIGHS)

09:33.500 --> 09:36.500
Hey, Dylan. You forgot this.

09:37.875 --> 09:39.333
I put his ear drops
in the front pouch

09:39.417 --> 09:41.792
-in case he runs a fever.
-BRIANNA DELRASSO: Hey.

09:41.875 --> 09:44.792
You better not be
talking about me, Erin.

09:44.875 --> 09:47.542
-I haven't said
nothing about you.
-Stop texting my man.

09:47.625 --> 09:50.834
'Cause he doesn't want anything
to do with you anymore. Okay?

09:50.917 --> 09:52.208
He's the father of my baby,

09:52.291 --> 09:54.583
so I kind of, like,
have to talk to him.

09:54.667 --> 09:55.667
BRIANNA: What's that?

09:55.750 --> 09:57.709
-Are you seriously that stupid?
-Fuck you, Erin!

09:57.792 --> 09:59.291
You know what?
You're gonna get it.

09:59.375 --> 10:00.291
Yeah. Trust me.

10:00.375 --> 10:01.709
When you least expect it,
you dumb bitch.

10:01.792 --> 10:03.542
DYLAN HINCHEY: Could you
please just put the window up?

10:03.625 --> 10:05.333
BRIANNA: No, I'm not gonna
fucking put the window up.

10:05.417 --> 10:07.083
-DYLAN: Brianna, Jesus Christ.
-(ERIN SIGHS)

10:07.458 --> 10:08.834
Stupid.

10:10.250 --> 10:11.250
Hey.

10:12.709 --> 10:14.959
We really need to schedule
his ear surgery.

10:15.041 --> 10:17.250
The doctor says
if he keeps getting infections,

10:17.333 --> 10:19.291
he could have hearing loss.

10:19.375 --> 10:20.834
Did you talk to your parents?

10:20.917 --> 10:22.750
Don't bring
my parents into this.
They do enough for him already.

10:22.834 --> 10:24.583
-Way more than your dad.
-You just said you'd talk
to your parents about--

10:24.667 --> 10:26.208
If I gotta pay more money,
it's gotta go through the court.

10:26.291 --> 10:27.959
-That's what we decided.
-That's gonna take forever.

10:28.041 --> 10:29.500
I mean, can we just
get his surgery done?

10:29.583 --> 10:31.667
-Just to make sure
that he's okay?
-DYLAN: I don't have $1,800

10:31.750 --> 10:33.333
-to meet the deductible, Erin!
-And then we can--

10:33.417 --> 10:35.208
How many times have I told you?

10:35.291 --> 10:37.625
Everything needs to go
through the court, okay?

10:37.709 --> 10:40.750
-I gotta go.
-(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

10:52.500 --> 10:56.458
Yeah, I'm looking for a--
for-- like a turtle tank.

10:56.542 --> 10:58.959
Do you have, like,
a tank for turtles?

10:59.041 --> 11:00.375
Yes, we do.

11:00.458 --> 11:02.500
Um, how about this one?

11:02.583 --> 11:05.166
This is the Amphibian Life 1500.

11:05.250 --> 11:07.291
This one's got
a UVB heating kit.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.375
This is a nice one.

11:09.458 --> 11:11.417
-And it's got--
-Yeah, I just-- I just need
something simple, really.

11:11.500 --> 11:14.834
It's a-- it's a--
it's a baby turtle.

11:14.917 --> 11:17.959
Okay. Um, all right.
Let's take a look over here.

11:20.208 --> 11:23.333
This one,
this is the Oasis Habitat.

11:23.417 --> 11:24.667
This is another nice setup.

11:24.750 --> 11:27.875
-Yeah, it also has--
-I think even simpler.

11:27.959 --> 11:30.000
I doubt the thing's
gonna live very long.

11:30.083 --> 11:31.375
Well, you'd be surprised.

11:31.458 --> 11:33.917
I mean, my mother's turtle
outlived her. (CHUCKLES)

11:34.000 --> 11:35.709
If it's taken care of, sure.

11:35.792 --> 11:37.208
If you feed it
and give it clean water

11:37.291 --> 11:39.667
and make sure it's not swimming
in his own filth.

11:42.583 --> 11:44.125
It's for my grandson.

11:44.208 --> 11:48.333
He's-- he's four and has trouble
focusing on tasks.

11:48.417 --> 11:50.625
I just-- yeah,
I don't think we need

11:50.709 --> 11:52.875
all the bells
and whistles is all.

11:54.500 --> 11:56.834
Have a look around.
I'll be up front.

11:59.542 --> 12:00.875
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

12:06.333 --> 12:07.417
This is Mare.

12:07.500 --> 12:10.083
TRAMMEL: Hey, Sarge,
this is, uh, Officer Trammel.

12:10.166 --> 12:12.500
We got a burglary
at 535 Argyle Road.

12:12.583 --> 12:14.208
Just tell her
it's Beth Hanlon's house.

12:14.291 --> 12:16.959
Uh, I'm gonna need you out
to process the scene.

12:17.041 --> 12:18.291
What happened?

12:18.375 --> 12:20.583
TRAMMEL: Homeowner came home
to find the trophy case smashed

12:20.667 --> 12:21.875
and some sports memorabilia
missing.

12:21.959 --> 12:23.083
BETH HANLON:
It's Freddie again, Mare.

12:23.166 --> 12:24.750
He's being his
fucking asshole self.

12:24.834 --> 12:26.750
She thinks maybe
it's her brother.

12:26.834 --> 12:28.208
Um, she caught him
in the basement

12:28.291 --> 12:30.875
shooting up last night
and threw him out.

12:30.959 --> 12:32.166
All right.

12:33.750 --> 12:35.375
Tell Beth I'm on my way.

12:37.208 --> 12:38.333
Excuse me.

12:39.709 --> 12:40.709
Yeah.

12:41.208 --> 12:43.542
That's perfect.

12:47.875 --> 12:51.542
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

12:55.417 --> 12:57.125
-Hey.
-FRANK SHEEHAN: Hey, Mare.

12:57.208 --> 12:58.709
How's your morning going so far?

12:58.792 --> 13:01.792
Great. I just, uh...

13:01.875 --> 13:05.792
wasted the last half hour
picking out an aquarium

13:05.875 --> 13:08.375
for the turtle you and Drew
brought home yesterday.

13:08.458 --> 13:09.750
FRANK:
He seems excited about it.

13:09.834 --> 13:11.542
I think it'll be good for him,
you know?

13:11.625 --> 13:13.208
Give him something
to look after.

13:13.291 --> 13:16.166
(CHUCKLES) That's what you said
about the lizard.

13:16.250 --> 13:18.500
Two weeks later, I was flushing
it down the toilet.

13:18.583 --> 13:21.166
FRANK: (SIGHS) Did you really
flush it down the toilet?

13:21.250 --> 13:23.500
Yes, I did.

13:23.583 --> 13:26.000
-I'm busy, Frank.
-FRANK: Okay. All right.

13:26.083 --> 13:28.667
Uh, look, I won't hold you up.
I just, um...

13:28.750 --> 13:30.834
(CLEARS THROAT)
I wanted to let you know

13:30.917 --> 13:34.166
that last night,
Faye and I-- uh, well...

13:34.250 --> 13:37.041
-FRANK: I asked Faye--
-Frank, I got--

13:37.125 --> 13:40.000
75-51 Delcom. I got eyes
on the burglary suspect

13:40.083 --> 13:41.750
200 block of Glen Riddle,
heading east.

13:41.834 --> 13:43.625
Black male wearing,
uh, blue jeans

13:43.709 --> 13:45.083
and a hooded sweatshirt.

13:46.417 --> 13:48.417
Freddie. Freddie Hanlon.

13:54.166 --> 13:55.250
Freddie!

14:00.625 --> 14:01.959
(GROANS)

14:07.125 --> 14:09.333
(GROANS) Goddamn it.

14:09.417 --> 14:11.542
Fuck. Fuck!

14:11.625 --> 14:13.750
Fucking thing. Fuck.

14:18.625 --> 14:20.917
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

14:24.917 --> 14:27.125
(PANTING)

14:34.125 --> 14:35.166
Freddie?

14:38.667 --> 14:40.709
(PANTING)

14:44.250 --> 14:45.542
(DOOR UNLOCKING)

14:47.583 --> 14:49.208
(WHISPERING)
No, don't. Put it away.

14:54.166 --> 14:55.166
Shh.

14:56.792 --> 14:58.875
Freddie?
(WHISPERING) Be careful.

15:01.000 --> 15:03.375
-Freddie?
-(CLATTERING)

15:03.458 --> 15:04.583
Come on out,

15:04.667 --> 15:07.333
so we can get a look at
where the blood's coming from.

15:09.625 --> 15:10.667
Freddie?

15:11.750 --> 15:14.375
Freddie,
don't make me call in the K9.

15:14.458 --> 15:15.959
(SIGHS) He's 11 years old

15:16.041 --> 15:18.208
and I think his mind's
starting to leave him.

15:22.208 --> 15:23.417
Freddie, come on.

15:26.166 --> 15:28.208
You have two minutes, all right?

15:34.917 --> 15:36.041
(SIGHS)

15:43.250 --> 15:44.417
What's the matter?

15:44.500 --> 15:45.667
The sight of blood.

15:45.750 --> 15:47.458
MARE: Don't look at it, then.
Get out of the doorway.

15:47.542 --> 15:50.417
Come on. Sit down.
Hurry up. Come on.

15:51.542 --> 15:52.792
Put your head
between your knees.

