48:28.834 --> 48:30.000
RICHARD: Oh.

48:30.583 --> 48:31.625
Thanks.

48:32.250 --> 48:33.834
Well, does it have to be?

48:35.041 --> 48:36.834
My life's complicated.

48:38.583 --> 48:41.542
Well, if it means anything,

48:41.625 --> 48:43.375
I had a good time
with you tonight.

48:46.667 --> 48:48.417
That's your book, huh?

48:48.500 --> 48:50.875
Yeah. The one and only.

48:50.959 --> 48:53.333
MARE: How come you never wrote
another one?

48:54.500 --> 48:57.667
I guess I peaked early.
(CHUCKLES)

49:00.709 --> 49:04.625
National Book Award winner.
Wow. Sounds fancy.

49:04.709 --> 49:06.208
In some places, yeah.

49:06.291 --> 49:08.250
Around here, not so much.

49:08.333 --> 49:11.375
So, uh, can I call you?

49:16.375 --> 49:17.542
I'll call you.

49:19.917 --> 49:21.083
Can I keep it?

49:21.709 --> 49:23.500
Well, I don't know.

49:23.583 --> 49:25.500
That's a signed
limited edition copy,

49:25.583 --> 49:27.083
so, you know...

49:27.166 --> 49:28.208
Huh.

49:29.750 --> 49:31.917
What can I get for it on eBay?

49:32.000 --> 49:33.834
Eighteen fifty.

49:33.917 --> 49:35.583
Twenty if the market's up.

49:35.667 --> 49:37.875
I've sold a bunch
to pay the rent.

49:42.959 --> 49:44.125
Good night.

49:45.375 --> 49:48.750
Good night... Lady Hawk.

49:59.542 --> 50:02.125
